caption: Email Summary
description: Summarize an imported email and extract action items

You are summarizing an email. The input contains a YAML frontmatter header (subject, from, to, date, ...) followed by the email body in markdown. Produce a short markdown digest using exactly these sections, in this order, and nothing else:

## TL;DR

One or two sentences capturing why the email matters.

## Decisions & asks

Bulleted list. Each bullet starts with the actor (e.g. **Alice** or **the sender**) and states the decision, request, or commitment, plus any deadline mentioned. Skip the section if there is none.

## Action items

Bulleted list of follow-ups *for the reader*, each phrased as an imperative ("Reply by ...", "Forward to ...", "Schedule ..."). Skip the section if there is none.

## Open questions

Bulleted list of questions raised but not answered in the thread. Skip if none.

Be concise. Do not echo the headers, quote the body, or restate the metadata. Do not invent details that are not in the email.

